05650nam a22009255i 9783110921731DE-B159720211217065530.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211217t20122007gw     fo  d z      ger d  a(OCoLC)1013951018  a97831109217317 a10.1515/97831109217312doi  a(DE-B1597)57076  a(OCoLC)840442071  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 ager  agwcDE 4aPN2051b.T73 2007 7aLIT0041702bisacsh04a792.16222/ger  aGE 85012rvk0(DE-625)rvk/39326:00aTransformationen des Religiösen :bPerformativität und Textualität im geistlichen Spiel /chrsg. von Ingrid Kasten, Erika Fischer-Lichte. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2012] 4c©2007  a1 online resource (287 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aTrends in Medieval Philology ,x1612-443X ;v110 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDie geistlichen Spiele, die in vielen europäischen Kulturen des Mittelalters bis in die Moderne nachweisbar sind, stehen in engem Zusammenhang mit Frömmigkeitspraktiken und beziehen ihre Sujets aus dem Kult, aus der Bibel und Legenden. Die Beiträge des interdisziplinären Sammelbandes nehmen geistliche Spiele als cultural performances und Teil einer multimedialen Frömmigkeitspraxis in den Blick. Sie fragen nach ihrer Stellung in der mittelalterlichen Alltags- und Festkultur, nach der Relation von Geistlichem und Weltlichem und nach der Inszenierung von kulturellen Ordnungsmodellen in den Spielen.  aThe religious plays found in many European cultures from the Middle Ages up until the modern age are closely related to devout practices and draw their subjects from worship, the bible and legends. The contributions to this interdisciplinary anthology take a look at religious plays as cultural performances and as part of a multimedia devout practice. The articles investigate the position of these plays within the culture of medieval daily life and festivity, the relationship between the spiritual and the secular, and the staging of cultural structural models in the plays.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aReligion in literaturexHistoryy16th centuryvCongresses. 0aTheaterxReligious aspectsxCatholic ChurchxHistoryy16th century. 4aGeistliches Drama. 4aPerformativität. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aReligious drama.  aperformativity.1 aEHRSTINE, GLENN, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEMING, JUTTA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aENDERS, JODY, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFISCHER-LICHTE, ERIKA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFischer-Lichte, Erika, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHERBERICHS, CORNELIA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKASTEN, INGRID, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKATRITZKY, Μ. Α., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKIENING, CHRISTIAN, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKOCH, ELKE, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKRÜGER, KLAUS, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKasten, Ingrid, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKotte, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRISI, CLEMENS, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aROSELT, JENS, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRÖCKE, WERNER, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSIMON, ECKEHARD, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook packa